<br>
&quot;It is certainly no cause for alarm. Large bodies routinely pass close to the Earth and only about half of near Earth asteroids are estimated to be known. A few doomsday cults might start putting up websites I suppose. Large asteroids strike the Earth only once a century on average and nothing near this size has struck the Earth for thousands of years. There is a higher chance of being struck by lightning but thats no reason to stay indoors.&quot;<br>
